The paper discusses the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques to improve intrusion detection systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Bayesian abductive reasoning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The involvement of the UMBC Accelerated Cognitive Computing Lab suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and neural networks (cs.NE).
